        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="EN">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="head">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        The Romanes neuer so matched and tamed, as bie Annibal a long time. And therefore his Historie the more notable in manie weightie respects.
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <person name="Hannibal"/>
                </position>
            </language>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia anchor_text="Saguntu[m] summa ui oppugnabat[ur]" hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Sagunti famosa oppugnatio.
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <location name="Saguntum"/>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>The famous attack of Saguntum.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="right_margin">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Nec mora hîc: nec requies. Nulla[e] nota[e] ipsi auctori pares: ne aphorismi quidem, aut discursus acerrimi. 
                        Adeò est ipse acutior ad huc, atq[ue] profundior.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Let there be no delay at this point, and no rest. No annotations can match the author himself: 
                not even the sharpest aphorisms or discussions. So much more acute and profound is he himself.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
